changes following a version update.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Investigating Jackson warnings**\\n\\nI'm noticing warnings about unknown enum constants related to Jackson, perhaps due to missing annotations. They might not be errors, but I wonder if adding the jackson-annotations library would resolve the warnings, even if it's not absolutely necessary. There could also be an issue with references to javax.servlet versus jakarta.servlet since version 3.0 switched to jakarta. Some classes may require the jakarta.servlet-api, which isn't transitive. It might be helpful to inspect class dependencies using jdeps on the jar, although I need to ensure it's in my Gradle cache.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_r1WkrQ9txDFY8X5y9f1GgmpE|fc_0402b21f18a18055016a42746da8e08193954ccc266d267bf1", "name": "bash", "arguments": {"command": "tmp=$(mktemp -d); cd \"$tmp\"; curl -sSfLO https://repo1.maven.org/maven2/org/springframework/boot/spring-boot-actuator/3.0.0/spring-boot-actuator-3.0.0.jar; jdeps --ignore-missing-deps -summary spring-boot-actuator-3.0.0.jar | sort", "timeout": 60}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 2464, "output": 520, "cacheRead": 17408, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 20392, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1782740068417, "responseId": "resp_0402b21f18a18055016a427464e7a4819399a54fd885097dff"}, "toolResults": [{"role": "toolResult", "toolCallId": "call_r1WkrQ9txDFY8X5y9f1GgmpE|fc_0402b21f18a18055016a42746da8e08193954ccc266d267bf1", "toolName": "bash", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "spring-boot-actuator-3.0.0.jar -> java.base\nspring-boot-actuator-3.0.0.jar -> java.management\nspring-boot-actuator-3.0.0.jar -> java.naming\nspring-boot-actuator-3.0.0.jar -> java.sql\nspring-boot-actuator-3.0.0.jar -> not found\n"}], "isError": false, "timestamp": 1782740079073}]}
